<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Lieutenant General <persName type="from">Alvan C.
                                    Gillem, Jr.</persName>, to Mr. <persName type="to">Walter S.
                                    Robertson</persName>, at Peiping</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-04">4 April 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>435. Chou En-lai has brought to my attention alleged incident which
                            occurred in Peiping on April 3rd when several Communist buildings were
                            searched and 39 people were arrested. What is your version?</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>